### Available Actions

Once the node is running, the following actions are available via the REST API:

| Action | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `aspirate` | Aspirate liquid from a well or current position |
| `dispense` | Dispense liquid into a well or current position |
| `transfer` | Transfer liquid from source well to destination well |
| `pick_up_tips` | Pick up disposable tips from the tip rack |
| `drop_tips` | Drop current tips into the waste |
| `get_handler_status` | Get current liquid handler status |

### Using the Interface Directly

The interface can be used independently of MADSci:

```python
from {{ module_name }}_interface import {{ module_name | pascal_case }}Interface

# Create and connect
interface = {{ module_name | pascal_case }}Interface()
interface.connect()
interface.initialize()

# Liquid handling operations
interface.pick_up_tips()
interface.aspirate(100.0, well="A1")
interface.dispense(100.0, well="B1")
interface.transfer(50.0, source_well="A2", dest_well="B2")
interface.drop_tips()

# Check status
status = interface.get_status()

# Clean shutdown
interface.shutdown()
interface.disconnect()
```

